# `.harness/` — governance state

This directory holds the **state and rules** of the harness governance protocol described in [../AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md). Everything in here is committed to the repo so that **any contributor can clone and immediately know where iteration is**.

## File map

| Path | Role | Lifetime |
|---|---|---|
| [CURRENT.md](CURRENT.md) | Pointer: `idle` or `in_progress: <task-id>` | Always present; mutates |
| [workflow.md](workflow.md) | The two-session protocol — coordinator and implementer steps | Stable |
| [triage.md](triage.md) | Coordinator triage rubric (light path vs full path) | Stable |
| [MEMORY.md](MEMORY.md) | Cross-task conventions / pitfalls / decisions / open questions | Grows over time |
| [templates/task-brief.md](templates/task-brief.md) | Template for `active/<task-id>.md` | Stable |
| [templates/start-coordinator.md](templates/start-coordinator.md) | Opening prompt for a coordinator session | Stable |
| [templates/start-implementer.md](templates/start-implementer.md) | Opening prompt for an implementer session | Stable |
| [active/](active/) | In-progress task briefs (one `.md` per task) | Per-task |
| [archive/](archive/) | Completed task briefs | Per-task |

## Lifecycle

```
idle ─[coordinator]─→ active/<id>.md created ─[implementer phase loop]─→ Final summary written ─→ archive/<id>.md
```

Only **one task** is in progress at a time. The protocol prevents starting a new coordinator session while `CURRENT.md` is `in_progress`.

## How to interact

Don't edit these files by hand unless you know exactly what you're doing. Use the helper:

```bash
harness start              # begin a new iteration (coordinator)
harness implement <id>     # resume an in-progress task (implementer)
harness status             # show CURRENT.md + active brief
harness end                # archive completed task → idle
harness remember "<text>"  # append to MEMORY.md
harness curate-memory      # quarterly cleanup
```

The `harness` CLI is installed globally (`~/.local/bin/harness` via `install.sh`); run `harness help` for the full subcommand reference.

## Maintenance discipline

- `MEMORY.md`: re-curate at least quarterly; entries must cite a source; hard size limit ~200 lines.
- `archive/`: keep all entries — they're the audit trail. Don't delete archived briefs even if features were reverted.
- `active/`: should always contain at most one file (plus `.gitkeep`).
